,"iconColor":{"opac":1,"rgb":"#000"},"text":{"rType":"text","val":"The terms gender sensitive indicators and gender responsive indicators are often used interchangeably and used in monitoring and evaluating policies, programmes and projects with a focus on gender. Although related, they have nuanced differences in purpose, focus and application. Therefore, description of the two is useful for clear understanding of the selected terminology. \nGiven the significance and complementarity of both indicators, a general term “gender indicators” will be used in referring to both. "}},"JCcz5HDny":{"type":"point","id":"JCcz5HDny","spotPosition":{"x":516,"y":516},"icon":{"selectedKey":13},"size":{"selectedKey":"m"},"iconColor":{"opac":1,"rgb":"#000"},"text":{"rType":"text","val":"Gender indicators can be classified based on the data and information sources, which can be qualitative or quantitative data, thus indicators can be termed as quantitative or qualitative indicators."}},"137YayLgX":{"type":"point","id":"137YayLgX","spotPosition":{"x":943,"y":516},"icon":{"selectedKey":13},"size":{"selectedKey":"m"},"iconColor":{"opac":1,"rgb":"#000"},"text":{"rType":"text","val":"Indicators are also categorised based on what they are intended to measure in policies, programmes and projects. Therefore, there are input, output, outcome, process, impact, and efficiency, effectiveness, performance, context and sustainability indicators. "}}},"p":["0mlOgVzEF","JCcz5HDny","137YayLgX"]}}},"sI4U-ZScZW":{"id":"sI4U-ZScZW","type":"interactive","subtype":"interactiveLinkedImages","setup":{"imgs":{"i":{"29HacGGVE":{"type":"image","id":"29HacGGVE","name":{"rType":"text","val":"Scene 1"},"bg":{"selectedKey":"fill","fill":{"opac":1,"rgb":"#bd8e71"}},"style":{"selectedKey":"textOverlapping"},"txtBg":{"fill":{"opac":0,"rgb":"#000"}},"desc":{"rType":"richtext","val":{"ops":[{"insert":"GESI indicators","attributes":{"bold":true,"color":"#ffffff"}},{"insert":"\n","attributes":{"size":"large"}}]},"hali":"","paddV1":12},"e":{"i":{"-pB4TdMxc":{"type":"element","id":"-pB4TdMxc","link":{"selectedKey":"image","val":"nuUZoCb-O"},"animation":{"selectedKey":"fade"},"pos":{"x":970,"y":200},"icon":{"selectedKey":14},"size":{"selectedKey":"m"},"iconColor":{"opac":1,"rgb":"var(--TC3)"}}},"p":["-pB4TdMxc"]}},"nuUZoCb-O":{"type":"image","id":"nuUZoCb-O","name":{"rType":"text","val":"Scene 2"},"bg":{"selectedKey":"fill","fill":{"opac":1,"rgb":"var(--TC7)"}},"style":{"selectedKey":"textOverlapping"},"txtBg":{"fill":{"opac":0,"rgb":"var(--TC7)"}},"desc":{"rType":"richtext","val":{"ops":[{"insert":"Indicators are key criteria or measures used to assess change. They can take the form of data points, facts, numbers, opinions, or perceptions, all serving as markers of changes in specific conditions or progress toward defined objectives. In the context of gender, indicators are tools specifically designed to track progress in achieving gender equality.","attributes":{"color":"var(--TC14)"}},{"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Gender indicators can be organized into different categories or levels, each reflecting distinct aspects of gender-related progress.","attributes":{"color":"var(--TC14)"}},{"insert":"\n","attributes":{"size":"normal"}}]},"hali":"","paddV1":7},"e":{"i":{"eX-3OzkIY":{"type":"element","id":"eX-3OzkIY","link":{"selectedKey":"image","val":"29HacGGVE"},"animation":{"selectedKey":"fade"},"pos":{"x":970,"y":200},"icon":{"selectedKey":18},"size":{"selectedKey":"m"},"iconColor":{"opac":1,"rgb":"var(--TC3)"}}},"p":["eX-3OzkIY"]}}},"p":["29HacGGVE","nuUZoCb-O"]}}}},"v":"1"}